items.synopsis: England score quickly before lunch on day three of the fifth Ashes Test at The Oval, putting Australia's misfiring bowlers firmly on the back foot. Follow live.

title.children: Australia's bowlers toil as England race ahead on day three of fifth Test

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A brutal session for Australia and potentially a match-winning morning for England. Led by Zak Crawley, the hosts scored at better than five runs an over yet again and Australia's bowlers are scratching their heads as to how to get them out. Crawley looks incredibly at ease out there and the plans seem completely ineffective. Stokes is partnering him, and that's terrifying too, because this innings matters and that probably means the England skipper is on for a big one. Australia needs four or five wickets in the next session to rein this in.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: England 1-130 (Crawley 71, Stokes 12)

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It was a classic swing bowler's wicket, angling in, pitching full and swinging away, just catching the slightest edge as Ben Duckett tried to crush a straight drive. Not sure who gets credit for the review, because a lot of people were talking, although Alex Carey and Marnus Labuschagne definitely seemed in favour of sending it upstairs. Ben Stokes comes out, rather than the injured Moeen Ali, who has been off the field for too long to bat in the top order.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Australia nails the review and Mitchell Starc breaks through!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: France win an epic. Inspirational captain Wendie Renard with the winner after a topsy turvy game. France were dominant in the first half and looked good for their 1-0 lead, but as the game stretched in the second half, Brazil began to take ascendency, and deserved to equalise. It came down to Renard wanting it more at a corner to settle this one. Brazil will still hope to progress, but this is a real dampener after their Joga bonito magic against Panama.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: France 2 - 1 Brazil

children.content: France win an epic.
Inspirational captain Wendie Renard with the winner after a topsy turvy game.
France were dominant in the first half and looked good for their 1-0 lead, but as the game stretched in the second half, Brazil began to take ascendency, and deserved to equalise.
It came down to Renard wanting it more at a corner to settle this one. Brazil will still hope to progress, but this is a real dampener after their Joga bonito magic against Panama.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's Wendie Renard, the captain, making the run from a corner and heading past the keeper. Inspirational from the irrepresible centre-back, who is the 7th highest scorer for France. Can't emphasise enough how good that run was, to get on the end of that, she almost ran in a semi-circle so smash it into the ground and into the net.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 84' GOAAAAAAAAAAL FRANCE!! Is that the winner?
